        "mainbody": "'''''Stormlight''''', by [[Ed Greenwood]], is the fourteenth book of the loosely-related [[The Harpers series]].\n\n{{quote|''Strange magic is on the loose in [[Firefall Keep]]—magic that kills.''\n\n''The mightiest War Wizards are baffled, and the shadow of destruction threatens valiant [[Harpers]] and nobles of the fair realm of [[Cormyr]] alike. With [[Harpers]] in jeopardy, it is up to the legendary [[Bard]] of Shadowdale, [[Storm Silverhand]], to overcome this lethal and mysterious force.''\n\n''\"Whenever I think I can relax at last, someone hastens to brutally point out to me that I've fresh work to do. It's time to save the world again.\" —[[Storm Silverhand]]''}}",
        "Summary": "{{Stub}}\n\n\nWhen [[Bane]] conquered the mind of a [[marilith]], he discovered Maxan Maxer, [[Storm Silverhand|Storm Silverhand's]] beloved, who the marileth had killed and then raised. He took over his body shortly before the [[Time of Troubles]]. When Bane was killed, a twisted fragment of him remained in Maxan, killing Athlan Summerstar, a minor Cormyrean noble and [[Harpers|Harper]]      and drawing the attention of Storm Silverhand. From Athlan, he learned the power to subsume, and began slaughtering servants, soldiers, War Wizards, and nobles until eventually Storm Silverhand forced him to destroy himself when she almost learned the secrets of the man who became Bane, freeing Maxer. The few survivors include the [[War Wizards|War Wizard]] Broglan, the heiress Shayna Summerstar, and the [[Purple Dragons|Purple Dragon]] commander Ergluth Rowanmantle.",
